#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:523
msgid "Death of Krawg"
msgstr "Mort de Kzawg"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:380
msgid "Kawn"
msgstr "Kawn"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:400
msgid "I see a house in the distance!"
msgstr "Je vois une maison au loin !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:415
msgid "Go away, you birds! Or I shall burn you out of the air!"
msgstr "Allez-vous en, sales oiseaux ! Ou je vous grille dans les airs même !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:419
msgid ""
"He doesn't want to talk to the gryphons, apparently. I think we'll have to "
"get someone there he will talk to..."
msgstr ""
"Il ne veut pas parler aux griffons, apparemment. Je crois que nous allons "
"devoir trouver quelqu'un avec qui il parlera... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:437
msgid "Thursagan"
msgstr "Thursagan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:443
msgid "What do you people want!? Leave me alone!"
msgstr "Que me voulez-vous !?! Laissez moi seul !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:447
msgid ""
"Old mage, we come with a message from Lord Durstorn. He asks you to come "
"back to the city."
msgstr ""
"Vieux mage, nous venons avec un message du Seigneur Durstorn. Il demande que "
"vous rentriez à la cité."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:451
msgid ""
"Ha! That fool thinks he can order me around. Why does he want me to go back, "
"anyway?"
msgstr ""
"Ha ! Ce fou pense qu'il peut me commander. Et pourquoi veut-il que je "
"rentre ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:455
msgid ""
"We have entered into a bargain with the king of Wesnoth to craft a sceptre "
"for him."
msgstr ""
"Nous avons conclu un marché avec le roi de Wesnoth. Nous devons lui "
"fabriquer un sceptre. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:459
msgid ""
"Oh, and now I suppose Durstorn wants me to craft it, eh? Well I'm not going "
"to."
msgstr ""
"Oh, et maintenant, je suppose que Durstorn veut que ce soit moi qui le "
"forge, hein ? Eh bien, je n'en ai pas l'intention."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:463
msgid ""
"You don't want to make a sceptre to contain the power of the ruby of fire? "
"Very well, your choice is made."
msgstr ""
"Vous ne voulez pas faire un sceptre contenant le pouvoir du Rubis de Feu ? "
"Très bien, votre choix est fait."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:467
msgid "The ruby of fire, what is that, some worthless Wesnothian gem?"
msgstr ""
"Le Rubis de Feu, qu'est-ce que c'est, une pierre wesnothienne sans intérêt ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:471
msgid ""
"It is a Wesnothian gem, but it is also supposedly the most powerful magical "
"artifact ever seen. Even an untrained hand can use it to cast fiery bolts as "
"powerful as those of arch mages."
msgstr ""
"C'est en effet une pierre précieuse wesnothienne, mais elle est également "
"censée être l'artéfact magique le plus puissant jamais vu. Même une main non "
"entraînée peut l'utiliser pour lancer des boules de feu aussi puissantes que "
"celles des archimages. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:475
msgid "Oh, really? And what does Haldric want us to do with it?"
msgstr "Oh, vraiment ? Et qu'est-ce qu'Haldric veut que nous en fassions ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:479
msgid "Contain and intensify its power."
msgstr "Contenir et intensifier son pouvoir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:483
msgid ""
"I see. Fine then, I will help you craft this sceptre... into the most "
"powerful magic artifact ever seen. This will be a true test of my skill. I "
"expect it will take many years."
msgstr ""
"Je vois. Très bien, je vous aiderai à façonner ce sceptre... en l'artéfact "
"magique le plus puissant jamais vu. Ce sera un vrai test pour mes aptitudes. "
"Je m'attends à ce que cela prenne de nombreuses années. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:487
msgid ""
"Good. Now, there are still wild animals here... we have to get back into the "
"caves."
msgstr ""
"Bien. Maintenant, il y a toujours des animaux sauvages par ici ... nous "
"devons retourner dans les caves."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:507
msgid "Move Thursagan to the signpost"
msgstr "Déplacer Thursagan jusqu'au panneau indicateur"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:97
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:296
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:151
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:380
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:127
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:374
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:488
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:548
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:165
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:457
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:830
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:60
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:527
msgid "Death of Thursagan"
msgstr "Mort de Thursagan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3_Searching_for_the_Runecrafter.cfg:545
msgid "Well, now we are in the caves again! Come on, back south, to the city."
msgstr ""
"Voila, nous sommes de nouveau dans les caves ! Allons-y, cap au sud, vers la "
"cité ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:3
msgid "The Council Regathers"
msgstr "Réunion du Conseil"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:39
msgid ""
"The path back was less dangerous than it was a year earlier. It did not take "
"them so long. So they quickly returned to the dwarven city, with two new "
"members of their party - one expected, and one not."
msgstr ""
"Le retour fut moins dangereux que l'aller ne l'avait été un an auparavant. "
"Il leur prit moins de temps. Ils rentrèrent donc rapidement à la cité des "
"nains, avec deux nouveaux membres à l'expédition. L'un que l'on attendait, "
"l'autre pas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:121
msgid "Lord Durstorn, we have succeeded in our mission. Thursagan is here."
msgstr ""
"Seigneur Durstorn, nous avons accompli notre mission. Thursagan est ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:125
msgid ""
"What? You mean you found Thursagan and got him to return with you? "
"Astounding! But what is that gryphon doing there?"
msgstr ""
"Quoi ? Vous voulez dire que vous avez trouvé Thursagan et que vous l'avez "
"ramené avec vous ? Incroyable ! Mais qu'est-ce que ce griffon fait ici ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:129
msgid "Yes, we did. And that is Krawg, who helped us in the northlands."
msgstr ""
"Oui, c'est ce que nous avons fait. Et voici Krawg, qui nous a aidés dans les "
"territoires du nord."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:133
msgid "Yaa! Mee Krawg!"
msgstr "Koui ! moa Krawg !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:137
msgid "Now, where is this ruby that I am to work with, eh Durstorn?"
msgstr ""
"Bon, et maintenant, où est ce rubis avec lequel je dois travailler, hein "
"Durstorn ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:141
msgid ""
"In the treasury. And leave it there until you're ready to work with it - I "
"still don't trust you."
msgstr ""
"Au trésor. Et laisse le là tant que tu n'es pas prêt à y travailler - Je ne "
"te fais toujours pas confiance. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:145
msgid "Ha! _You_ don't trust _me_?"
msgstr "Ha! _Tu_ ne _me_ fais pas confiance ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:149
msgid ""
"Exactly! Why would I? And I order you to stay out of the treasury, away from "
"that ruby!"
msgstr ""
"Exactement ! Comment le pourrais-je ? Et je t'ordonne de rester loin du "
"trésor et loin du rubis !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:153
msgid ""
"You don't dictate what I am to do, Durstorn! I will do as I please, and "
"don't stop me if you want me to make this sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Tu ne me dicteras pas ce que j'ai à faire, Durstorn ! Je ferais ce que je "
"veux. N'essaye pas de m'en empêcher si tu veux que je fasse ce sceptre. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:157
msgid "The ruby is mine, and don't touch it!"
msgstr "Le rubis est à moi, ne le touche pas !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Uh, technically it's Haldric's, and I think that if Thursagan needs to see "
"to plan this sceptre, he can."
msgstr ""
"Euh, techniquement il appartient à Haldric et je pense que si Thursagan a "
"besoin de voir le rubis pour dessiner les plans de son sceptre, qu'il le "
"fasse. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:165
msgid "Fine. *grumble grumble*"
msgstr "Bien, puisque c'est comme ça ..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:171
msgid ""
"Hm... a most interesting jewel. I can feel its magical power. I will start "
"drawing up plans for the sceptre immediately."
msgstr ""
"Hm... C'est un bijou très intéressant. Je sens son pouvoir magique. Je vais "
"immédiatement commencer à dessiner les plans immédiatement."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:180
msgid "Now, I will need certain materials to make this sceptre."
msgstr "Hum, je vais avoir besoin de certains matériaux pour faire ce sceptre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:184
msgid "Oh, what?"
msgstr "Oh, lesquels ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:188
msgid ""
"I would say probably ten stone of artifact-quality gold and twenty stone of "
"the finest coal, and many of the finest jewels in the land - we'll need "
"others to search for those, though. I'll also need to have the jeweler cut "
"the ruby once I have the plans done."
msgstr ""
"Je dirais probablement dix pierres d'or de qualité artéfact et vingt pierres "
"du charbon le plus pur, et beaucoup des plus fines pierres précieuses du "
"pays - nous aurons besoin que d'autres les cherchent. J'aurais aussi besoin "
"que le bijoutier taille le rubis une fois les plans faits. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:192
msgid ""
"Just use my gold and coal, I have enough! Or, if they're not 'good enough' "
"for you, find them yourself."
msgstr ""
"Utilise mon or et mon charbon, j'en ai assez ! Ou bien, s'ils ne sont pas "
"'assez purs' pour toi, trouves-en toi-même."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:196
msgid ""
"You try my patience, Durstorn. You know yours aren't acceptable, but you "
"have to give me something or I can't make the sceptre!"
msgstr ""
"Tu essayes de tester ma patience, Durstorn. Tu sais que leur qualité n'est "
"pas suffisante, mais tu devras quand même me donner quelque chose, ou je ne "
"pourrais pas faire le sceptre !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:200
msgid ""
"Wait, wait. The gold and coal... I think we can find those in the abandoned "
"eastern mines. Trolls have overrun them, but earlier they were the source of "
"the finest smithing materials."
msgstr ""
"Attends, attends. L'or et le charbon... Je pense qu'on peut les trouver dans "
"les mines abandonnées de l'est. Les trolls les ont envahies, mais avant, "
"elles étaient la source des meilleurs matériaux de forge. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:204
msgid "So, we will go to the eastern mines!"
msgstr "Bien, nous irons donc dans les mines de l'est !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Fine. As for the jewels, I will have others obtain those. That will cost "
"quite a bit of our payment, but it can't be helped. Our people do not mine "
"jewels."
msgstr ""
"Bien. Et pour les pierres précieuses, je m'arrangerai pour que d'autres les "
"obtiennent. Cela va nous coûter une bonne partie du payement, mais on ne "
"peut pas faire autrement. Notre peuple n'extrait pas les pierres précieuses. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:212
msgid ""
"That is acceptable. Durstorn, send some miners along with us to the Eastern "
"Mines, and I will bring some runecrafters-in-training from the academy to "
"help fight these enemies."
msgstr ""
"C'est acceptable. Durstorn, envoie quelques mineurs avec nous dans les mines "
"de l'est, et je prendrai quelques apprentis forgerons de runes de "
"l'académie. Ils nous aideront à combattre ces ennemis."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:219
msgid "Kinan"
msgstr "Kinan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:225
msgid "Rynan"
msgstr "Rynan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:228
msgid "Two runesmiths from the academy have joined you!"
msgstr "Deux forgerons de runes de l'académie vous ont rejoints !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:232
msgid ""
"Fine, you all go to the eastern mines. Me, I'll stay here. No point going "
"where I can't help!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, vous allez tous dans les mines de l'est. Moi, je reste ici. Pas "
"question que j'aille où je ne suis pas utile !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/3t_The_Coucil_Regathers.cfg:237
msgid "M' 'u!"
msgstr "Kouoi 'ssi ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:3
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:11
msgid "Gathering Materials"
msgstr "Rassembler les matériaux"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Those who went to the eastern mines were brave indeed. They were infested "
"with trolls and other vile creatures, who thrived in the dark and gloom of "
"the caves."
msgstr ""
"Ceux qui allèrent dans les mines de l'est étaient bien courageux. Elles "
"étaient infestées de trolls et d'autres horribles créatures, qui "
"grouillaient dans l'obscurité des caves."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:24
msgid ""
"And braver still were Rugnur and his companions, who had to spend two years "
"in those tunnels. For mining is a lengthy business. But they could for the "
"most part avoid the enemy. They only once had to venture into the very heart "
"of the trolls' territory."
msgstr ""
"Et courageux furent aussi Rugnur et ses compagnons qui passèrent presque "
"deux ans dans ces tunnels. Car extraire quelque chose de la terre est "
"toujours un travail long et fastidieux. Mais ils purent éviter la plupart "
"des ennemis. Ils ne s'aventurèrent qu'une seule fois au coeur du territoire "
"des trolls."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:48
msgid "Gather the necessary gold and coal to create the sceptre"
msgstr "Rassembler l'or et le charbon nécessaire à la création du sceptre"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:52
msgid "1 load of gold and 2 loads of coal are needed"
msgstr "1 chargement d'or et 2 chargements de charbon sont nécessaires"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:87
msgid ""
"Well, these are the eastern mines. Trolls and ogres live here, be prepared "
"to fight them; also be prepared to spend quite some time here - mining can "
"take a while."
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, voici les mines de l'est. Des trolls et des ogres ont vécu ici, "
"préparez-vous à en combattre ; préparez-vous aussi à rester un moment ici - "
"creuser peut prendre du temps."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:91
msgid ""
"For me to make the artifact Haldric wants, I need a special type of gold. I "
"do not know where it was found, but Baglur said these mines were the source "
"of it."
msgstr ""
"Pour que je puisse faire le sceptre qu'Haldric veut, j'ai besoin d'or d'un "
"genre spécial. Je ne sais pas où on le trouve, mais Baglur a dit que ces "
"mines en sont la source."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:95
msgid "Also, the only coal that will melt this gold is also here."
msgstr "De même, le seul charbon capable de faire fondre cet or est aussi ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:99
msgid ""
"So we're down here to, what, mine this gold and coal? That should be easy "
"enough."
msgstr ""
"Donc, nous sommes venus ici pour quoi, sortir cet or et ce charbon ? Ce sera "
"assez facile."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:103
msgid ""
"Yes, although we will have to hire the miners - they don't work for free. "
"But beware, there are trolls and such down here..."
msgstr ""
"Oui, bien que nous pourrions engager des mineurs - ils ne travaillent pas "
"gratuitement. Mais soyez conscient qu'il y a des trolls et d'autres choses "
"ici ... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:156
msgid "My load of coal is delivered!"
msgstr "Mon chargement de charbon est livré !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:174
msgid "That's the last load of coal we need."
msgstr "C'est le dernier chargement de charbon dont nous avons besoin."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:184
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:235
msgid ""
"This is all we need from these mines. Now we should go back further west, "
"where there are no trolls and ogres, and mine there."
msgstr ""
"C'est tout ce dont nous avons besoin dans ces mines. Maintenant, retournons "
"plus à l'ouest, là où il n'y a plus de trolls, d'ogres ou de mine."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:211
msgid "Here's the gold."
msgstr "Voici l'or. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:333
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:460
msgid "Here is some of the coal that we need! Bring the miners to take it!"
msgstr ""
"Voici une partie du charbon nécessaire ! Amenez les mineurs pour le prendre !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:347
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:474
msgid "I have all the coal I can carry..."
msgstr "J'ai tout le charbon que je peux porter..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:525
msgid "Here is the mine of precious gold! Send the miners this way."
msgstr "Voici la mine du précieux or ! Envoyez les mineurs par ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4_Gathering_Materials.cfg:539
msgid "I have all the gold I can carry..."
msgstr "J'ai tout l'or que je peux porter..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:3
msgid "The Jeweler"
msgstr "Le Bijoutier"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:41
msgid ""
"Rugnur and his companions returned home. Now, I do not want to give the "
"impression that only Rugnur and Thursagan worked on this masterpiece. There "
"were others - many others. Thus I present Theganli, the jeweler. His role is "
"small, but an important one."
msgstr ""
"Rugnur et ses compagnons retournèrent chez eux. Mais je ne veux pas donner "
"l'impression que seuls Rugnur et Thursagan travaillèrent sur le chef-"
"d'oeuvre. Il y en a eu d'autres - beaucoup d'autre. Donc je vais parler de "
"Theganli, le bijoutier. Son intervention a été courte, mais importante."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:115
msgid ""
"So, you have returned. I assume you have obtained the required materials? My "
"jeweler Theganli has spent the last two years buying jewels from some of the "
"northern clans. So now go to the forge and make your sceptre. What do you "
"need to annoy me for?"
msgstr ""
"Donc, vous êtes revenus. Je suppose que vous avez obtenu tous les matériaux "
"nécessaires ? Mon bijoutier Theganli a passé les deux dernières années à "
"acheter des pierres précieuses aux clans du nord. Maintenant, va forger le "
"sceptre. Pourquoi dois-tu encore m'ennuyer ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:119
msgid "We don't. Not everything is about you. We need to talk to Theganli."
msgstr ""
"Ce n'est pas notre intention. Tout ne tourne pas autour de toi. Nous avons "
"besoin de parler à Theganli."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:123
msgid ""
"That makes sense, I guess you would to plan the sceptre's design... what in "
"particular do you want him to do?"
msgstr ""
"Je comprends, je suppose que c'est pour dessiner les plans du sceptre... Que "
"voulez-vous qu'il fasse exactement ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:127
msgid ""
"I need to make the plans for the sceptre, then have him cut the ruby to "
"match them."
msgstr ""
"J'ai besoin qu'il taille le rubis de telle façon qu'il rentre dans les plans "
"du sceptre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:131
msgid "You're going to cut the jewel!? Are you insane?"
msgstr "Tu veux tailler dans le Joyau ? Tu es devenu fou ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:135
msgid ""
"What are you talking about, sir? You knew all along the jewel would have to "
"be cut to make the sceptre out of."
msgstr ""
"De quoi parlez-vous monsieur ? Vous saviez que le rubis devrait être taillé "
"pour rentrer dans le sceptre. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:139
msgid "Oh... right, right. Fine. Theganli?"
msgstr "Oh... oui, oui, c'est vrai. Très bien. Theganli ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:143
msgid "He's in his shop, in the southern tunnel."
msgstr "Il est dans son magasin, dans le tunnel du sud. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:147
msgid "Whatever. Kuhnar, go, summon him here."
msgstr "Peut importe. Kuhnar, va, et ramène-le ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:152
msgid ""
"Theganli! Come out of there, Durstorn orders you to come to the citadel."
msgstr "Theganli ! Viens par ici, Durstorn t'ordonne de venir à la citadelle."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:159
msgid "Theganli"
msgstr "Theganli"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:163
msgid "I'm coming... coming... stop pounding on the door..."
msgstr "Je viens, je viens ... Arrêtez de maltraiter cette porte... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:167
msgid ""
"He doesn't need to come here, I'll take the jewel to his shop. He'll need "
"his tools anyway."
msgstr ""
"Il n'a pas besoin de venir ici, je peux lui apporter la pierre à son "
"magasin. De toutes façons, il va avoir besoin de ses outils. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:197
msgid "Well, Theganli, what do you think of this jewel?"
msgstr "Bien, Theganli, que penses-tu de cette pierre précieuse ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:201
msgid "Uh, um, yes, yes, very impressive jewel, impressive, yes... "
msgstr ""
"Euh, hum, oui, oui, oui, très impressionnant, très impressionnant, oui..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:205
msgid "Do you think you could cut it in the manner my plans specify?"
msgstr ""
"Pensez-vous que vous pourrez le tailler de la façon dont mes plans le "
"prévoient ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:209
msgid "Well, uh, um, maybe... maybe... it will be hard... let me see..."
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, euh, hum, peut-être... peut-être... Ce ne sera pas facile... "
"Laissez-moi voir..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:213
msgid "Very well. See what you can do."
msgstr "Très bien. Voyez ce que vous pouvez faire. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:218
msgid ""
"Theganli spent many months cutting the jewels that would go into the Sceptre "
"of Fire, and the Ruby of Fire he attempted last. But he could not cut it."
msgstr ""
"Theganli consacra de nombreux mois à tailler les pierres qui devaient être "
"intégrées au Sceptre de Feu, et il s'essaya finalement au Rubis de Feu. Mais "
"il ne put pas le tailler. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:222
msgid "Well, do you have anything yet?!"
msgstr "Bien, avez-vous quelque chose pour moi !?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:226
msgid ""
"Ah, well, uh, no... no, not yet... unfortunately... it seems... it can't be "
"cut... or scratched... or damaged at all... at least not by my tools..."
msgstr ""
"Ah, eh bien, euh, non... non, pas encore... malheureusement... on dirait... "
"qu'il ne peut pas être coupé... ou griffé... ou même endommagé de quelque "
"manière.... en tout cas pas avec mes outils... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:230
msgid ""
"So what do you propose we do? We need this jewel cut in a very specific way "
"to make sure... well, it doesn't matter why."
msgstr ""
"Et que proposez-vous de faire ? Il faut que cette pierre soit taillée d'une "
"de cette façon particulière pour être sûr que... Euh, tout le monde s'en "
"fou... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:234
msgid ""
"Well... maybe... the Shorbear clan? They have good tools... yes, yes, they "
"do..."
msgstr ""
"Eh bien... peut-être... le clan Shorbear ? Ils ont de bons outils... oui, "
"oui, de bons outils..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:238
msgid "Who are they?"
msgstr "Qui sont-ils ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:242
msgid ""
"Another group... of dwarves... live south of here... above ground... yes... "
"best jewelers I know of... have special tools... tools, yes..."
msgstr ""
"Un autre groupe... de nains... qui vivent plus au sud... au-dessus du sol... "
"oui... les meilleurs tailleurs de pierres précieuses que je connaisse... ils "
"ont des outils spéciaux... des outils, oui... "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:246
msgid ""
"Well, Rugnur, what are you waiting for? Go down and get these tools from "
"them, and carve the jewel!"
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, Rugnur, Qu'attendez-vous ? Allez chercher ces outils chez eux, et "
"taillez le joyau."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:255
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:261
msgid ""
"We can't just go in there and take their property. We'll have to buy, or "
"rent, it from them."
msgstr ""
"Nous ne pouvons pas aller là et leur prendre leur propriété. Nous devrons "
"leur acheter, ou leur louer."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:267
msgid "Fine. Go rent it from them."
msgstr "D'accord. Allez leur en louer."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:271
msgid "Very well. We'll go south now."
msgstr "Très bien, nous partons immédiatement vers le sud."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:275
msgid ""
"Wait! Last time you made a bargain by yourself you lost us five thousand "
"pieces of silver. I'm going with you this time!"
msgstr ""
"Non, attends ! La dernière fois que tu as conclu un marché, nous avons perdu "
"cinq mille pièces d'argent. Cette fois, je viens avec toi !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:279
msgid "Are you sure that is wise, lord?"
msgstr "Vous êtes sûr que ce soit sage, seigneur ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:283
msgid ""
"Of course! To be safe, though, you and Noiraran are going to come with us."
msgstr "Bien sûr ! Pour plus de sécurité, toi et Noiranan venez avec nous. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/4t_The_Jeweler.cfg:287
msgid "Yes sir... *sigh*"
msgstr "Oui, chef... *gloups*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:3
msgid "Hills of the Shorbear Clan"
msgstr "Les Collines du clan Shorbear"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:30
msgid "Glonoin"
msgstr "Glonoin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:91
msgid ""
"All dwarves are known for a love of gold and a heart of stone. The shorbears "
"were no exception. They were crafters of crafters - they made tools. The "
"best in the land. And they bartered well."
msgstr ""
"On connait les nains pour leur amour de l'or et leur coeur de pierre. Les "
"Shorbears n'y faisaient pas exception. Ils étaient artisans pour les "
"artisans - ils fabriquaient des outils. Les meilleurs du royaume. Et ils "
"marchandaient bien."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:111
msgid "Defeat dwarvish leader"
msgstr "Abattre le leader nain"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:131
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:378
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:492
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:552
msgid "Death of Durstorn"
msgstr "mort de Durstorn"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:188
msgid ""
"Here we are; the hills of the Shorbear clan. What are we here for, anyway?"
msgstr ""
"Et voila ; les collines du clan Shorbear. Pourquoi sommes-nous ici, en "
"fait ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:192
msgid ""
"If I understand it correctly, we're here to bargain with the Shorbears, and "
"arrange for us to use their tools to cut the ruby."
msgstr ""
"Si j'ai bien compris, nous allons traiter avec les Shorbears, pour pouvoir "
"utiliser leurs outils pour couper le rubis. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:196
msgid "Exactly."
msgstr "Exactement."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:200
msgid ""
"And I'll be doing the talking; I remember what happened last time you "
"negotiated a deal! We lost five thousand pieces of silver."
msgstr ""
"Et je mènerai la négociation ; je me rappelle de ce qui s'est passé la "
"dernière fois que tu as conclu une affaire. Nous avons perdu cinq mille "
"pièces d'argent. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:204
msgid "Ay, its some of them cave-dwarves. What business do you have here?"
msgstr "Hé, on dirait des nains des sous-sols. Que venez-vous faire ici ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:208
msgid ""
"I'm Lord Durstorn, king of my tribe. I have been told you are great jeweler-"
"workers, and so we come to rent some of your tools for a short time, a few "
"years at most."
msgstr ""
"Je suis le seigneur Durstorn, roi de ma tribu. J'ai entendu dire que vous "
"étiez de grands joailliers, nous sommes donc venus vous louer des outils "
"pour une courte période, quelques années, tout au plus. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:212
msgid ""
"You're a king?! Must be a pretty small kingdom for you to come yourself to "
"bargain with us!"
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes un roi ?! Ce doit être un sacrément petit royaume pour que vous "
"veniez en personne négocier avec nous ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:216
msgid "You insult me! Do you want my business, or not?"
msgstr "Vous m'insultez ! Vous voulez discuter avec moi, ou pas ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:220
msgid "Well, fine, I'll hear your offer."
msgstr "Euh, oui, très bien, j'écouterai ce que vous avez à dire. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:224
msgid ""
"We'd like to rent your best tools for a short period of time. We'll only be "
"cutting one jewel with it. My starting offer is two hundred silver."
msgstr ""
"Nous voudrions louer vos meilleurs outils pour une courte période de temps. "
"Nous ne couperons qu'une seule pierre. Ma première offre est de deux cents "
"pièces d'argent. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:228
msgid ""
"It must be worth a lot for you to come this way and offer that much! How "
"much are you going to sell it for, eh?"
msgstr ""
"Cette pierre doit valoir beaucoup pour que vous veniez jusqu'ici m'offrir "
"une si grosse somme ! Vous allez la vendre combien, hein ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:232
msgid "That's none of your concern!"
msgstr "Cela ne vous concerne pas !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:236
msgid "I'll take twenty-five hundred, minimum."
msgstr "Ce sera deux mille cinq cents, minimum."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:240
msgid "(whispered) Durstorn, that would be a quarter of all our profits!"
msgstr "(soupir) Durstorn, ce serait déjà un quart de nos profits ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:244
msgid "I know that. Uh, Glonoin, how about five hundred?"
msgstr "Je le sais. Hum, Glonoin, pourquoi pas cinq cents ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:248
msgid ""
"Twenty-three hundred is my lowest offer. I can tell I don't need the money "
"as much as you need the jewel cut!"
msgstr ""
"Deux mille trois cents est mon meilleur prix. Et je pense que je n'ai pas "
"autant besoin de l'argent que vous n'avez besoin que ce joyau soit taillé ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:252
msgid "You must be mad! I'll offer one thousand, but no higher!"
msgstr "Vous devez être fou ! J'offrirai mille pièces, mais pas plus ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:256
msgid "Two thousand, and I'll go no lower!"
msgstr "Deux mille, et je ne descendrai pas plus bas."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:260
msgid "(whispered) What are we going to do? We can't go much higher!"
msgstr "(soupir) Qu'allons nous faire ? Nous ne pouvons pas monter plus ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:264
msgid ""
"(whispered) Offer him fifteen hundred, but don't go up, even if he refuses."
msgstr ""
"(soupir) Offrons-lui mille cinq cents pièces et n'allons pas plus loin, même "
"s'il refuse."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:268
msgid ""
"(whispered) Bah! Getting this cut isn't worth that much; what with Rugnur's "
"mistake earlier, and all the other expenses, if we pay more than a thousand "
"we'll barely even make a profit!"
msgstr ""
"(soupir) Bah ! Cette taille ne vaut pas autant, avec l'erreur de Rugnur et "
"toutes les autres dépenses, si nous payons plus que mille pièces, nous "
"n'aurons quasiment fait aucun profit !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:272
#, fuzzy
msgid "(whispered) So what are you going to do?"
msgstr "(soupir) Et donc, que faisons-nous ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:276
msgid "(whispered) Fight him, and take the tools by force."
msgstr "(soupir) Combattons-les et prenons-leur les outils de force. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:280
msgid "Are you mad?!?"
msgstr "Vous êtes fou ?!?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:284
msgid ""
"Of course not! Now, Glonoin; one thousand was my final offer. If you won't "
"accept it, we will take the tools from you by force!"
msgstr ""
"Bien sûr que non ! Glonoin ; mille pièces étaient ma dernière offre. Si vous "
"ne l'acceptez pas, nous vous prendrons les outils de force ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:288
msgid "I'd like to see you try!"
msgstr "Essayez seulement ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:292
msgid "You're making a mistake, Durstorn."
msgstr "Tu fais une erreur, Durstorn."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:296
msgid "Shut up, all of you! Attack them!"
msgstr "Taisez-vous tous ! Attaquez-les ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:306
msgid "Lyndar"
msgstr "Lyndar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:313
msgid ""
"Aha! I've spent years looking for you Dwarves, but now I've found you! "
"Prepare to die!"
msgstr ""
"Aha ! J'ai passé des années à vous chercher, nains, mais maintenant, je vous "
"ai trouvés ! Préparez-vous à mourir !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:317
msgid "Who the devil are you?"
msgstr "Qui diable êtes-vous ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:321
msgid ""
"I thought we left the elves behind at the gates four years ago! It seems we "
"have two enemies now."
msgstr ""
"Je pensais que nous avions laissé les elfes derrière une porte il y a quatre "
"ans ! On dirait que nous avons deux ennemis maintenant."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:325
msgid ""
"So, elves, are you against these dwarves too? They're attacking my clan for "
"absolutely no reason!"
msgstr ""
"Donc, elfes, vous êtes aussi contre ces nains ? Ils attaquent mon clan sans "
"aucune raison ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:329
msgid "I see. So you don't have the ruby?"
msgstr "Je vois. Donc, vous n'avez pas le rubis ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:333
msgid ""
"No, they do. They wanted to rent my tools to cut it, but they didn't offer "
"me nearly enough!"
msgstr ""
"Non. Ce sont eux qui l'ont. Ils voulaient me louer mes outils pour le "
"tailler, mais ils ne m'ont pas proposé assez ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:337
msgid ""
"How about this - I help you defeat them, and you let me keep the ruby when "
"we have?"
msgstr ""
"Que dites-vous de ça - Je vous aide à les combattre, et vous me laisser "
"garder le rubis quand nous l'avons ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:341
msgid "Deal!"
msgstr "Vendu ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:345
msgid "Ah, they don't scare me! We can take both of them!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, ils ne me font pas peur ! Nous pouvons les prendre tous les deux ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:349
msgid ""
"Don't be a fool! We can't take the elves, and it was a mistake to attack "
"these dwarves, but if we have to fight we should retreat once we get what we "
"came for, the tools!"
msgstr ""
"Ne soyez pas fou ! Nous ne pouvons pas combattre les elfes, et c'était une "
"erreur d'attaquer ces nains, mais si nous devons nous battre, nous devrions "
"repartir une fois que nous aurons eu ce que nous sommes venus chercher, les "
"outils !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:354
msgid "Defeat Glonoin, the Shorbear clan leader"
msgstr "Abattez Glonoin, le chef du clan Shorbear"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:358
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:472
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:532
msgid "Have all heroes in the Shorbear caves while no enemies are in the caves"
msgstr ""
"Déplacez tous les héros dans les sousterrains de Shorbear tant qu'aucun "
"ennemi n'y est."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:420
msgid "Ha! Now we can get those tools easily, and go back to our own caves."
msgstr ""
"Ha ! Maintenant, nous pouvons facilement prendre les outils et retourner "
"dans nos cavernes."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:424
msgid ""
"And how do you plan on doing that? There are elves swarming these hills, "
"trying to kill us."
msgstr ""
"Et comment comptez-vous faire ça ? Il y a des elfes qui rôdent dans ces "
"collines, qui veulent notre peau."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:428
msgid ""
"You are right... well, we will be able to break out eventually, and while "
"we're here, we'll be able to finally make the sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Tu as raison... Nous allons éventuellement pouvoir passer et, tant que nous "
"y sommes, nous allons finalement pouvoir faire le sceptre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:460
msgid ""
"Well, back to the battle - we are all in the caves, but there are still "
"enemies in here also!"
msgstr ""
"Bon, revenons à la bataille. Nous sommes tous dans les souterrains, mais il "
"y a encore des ennemis ici ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:464
msgid ""
"Indeed. Kill them! And make sure no more enter. Then we can close the gates."
msgstr ""
"Très juste. Tuez-les ! Et assurez-vous qu'aucun autre n'entre. Ensuite, nous "
"pourrons fermer les portes. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:504
msgid ""
"We have driven all of the dwarves and elves out of these caves. They are not "
"ours, though, and we can't stay here forever."
msgstr ""
"Nous avons bouté tous les nains et les elfes hors de ces cavernes. Ils ne "
"sont pas des nôtres de toute façon, et nous ne pouvons pas rester ici pour "
"toujours. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:508
msgid "True. I suspect these elves will try to besiege us here."
msgstr "En effet. Je suspecte que ces elfes vont essayer de nous assiéger ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:520
msgid ""
"Well, back to the battle - we need everyone to get into the Shorbear caves. "
"And then stop any enemies from coming in here."
msgstr ""
"Bon, revenons à la bataille - Il faut que tout le monde rentre dans les "
"cavernes de Shorbear. Et ensuite que l'on empêche les ennemis de rentrer. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:524
msgid "Indeed. Everyone to the caves, and kill those still inside!"
msgstr ""
"En effet. Tous dans les cavernes, et tuez tous ceux qui sont encore à "
"l'intérieur ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:606
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:678
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:728
msgid ""
"We have driven all of the dwarves and elves out of these caves! Now, seal "
"the gates!"
msgstr ""
"Nous avons bouté tous les nains et tous les elfes hors de ces cavernes ! "
"Maintenant, scellez les portes !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:92
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/5_Hills_of_the_Shorbear_Clan.cfg:747
msgid "Gaanngh..."
msgstr "Gaanngh..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:3
msgid "Towards the Caves"
msgstr "Vers les souterrains"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:30
msgid "Gaenlar"
msgstr "Gaenlar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:61
msgid "Glinan"
msgstr "Glinan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:88
msgid "Kalnar"
msgstr "Kalnar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:108
msgid ""
"Durstorn's rash action led to many problems. Not the least of which was "
"being surrounded by elves."
msgstr ""
"L'action irréfléchie de Durstorn amena de nombreux problèmes. Être encerclé "
"par les elfes ne fut pas le moindre d'entre eux."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:111
msgid ""
"The dwarves spent several years trapped in those caves, the elves besieging "
"them. The dwarves could not leave, for there were far too many elves, and "
"there was no way out of the caverns other than above ground. But the elves "
"could not enter, for the magical dwarven gates were closed."
msgstr ""
"Les nains ont passé plusieurs années enfermés dans ces cavernes, sous le "
"siège des elfes. Les nains ne pouvaient pas sortir, car il y avait trop "
"d'elfes, et il n'y avait pas d'autre sortie à ces cavernes que sous le sol. "
"Mais les elfes ne purent pas entrer, car les portes magiques des nains "
"étaient fermées. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:114
msgid ""
"During this time, Thursagan crafted the Sceptre of Fire, first cutting the "
"jewel, then putting it, the gold and the cold steel into the heat of the "
"flame. The sceptre was crafted, but something was not right. No matter what "
"enchantment of runes he put on the sceptre, it did not fulfil its original "
"purpose."
msgstr ""
"Pendant ce temps, Thursagan forgeait le sceptre, d'abord en taillant le "
"rubis, puis en le plaçant, ainsi que l'or et le charbon froid, au coeur de "
"la flamme. Le sceptre était prêt, mais quelque chose n'allait pas. Quel que "
"soit l'enchantement des runes qu'il mit sur le sceptre, il ne remplissait "
"pas son office."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:131
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:368
msgid "Move Rugnur to the northeast cave entrance"
msgstr "Déplacer Rugnur à l'entrée des cavernes au nord-est"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:135
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:457
msgid "Move Alanin to the southern border east of the river"
msgstr "Déplacer Alanin à rive sud de la rivière"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:182
msgid ""
"Well, Thursagan has reached a conclusion. He can't make the sceptre with the "
"materials he has here, but he has the final plans for it, and all the jewels "
"and gold he needs. Shouldn't we leave now?"
msgstr ""
"Bien, Thursagan a conclu. Il ne peut pas faire le sceptre avec le matériel "
"qui est ici, mais il a les plans définitifs et tout l'or et les bijoux dont "
"il a besoin. Ne devrions-nous pas partir maintenant ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:186
msgid ""
"All this time and he couldn't make it? Fine, we should try to leave... but "
"it's not like we could leave if we wanted to. We're surrounded!"
msgstr ""
"Tout ce temps et il n'a pas pu le faire ? Bon, nous devrions essayer de "
"partir... Mais ce n'est pas comme si nous pouvions partir si nous le "
"voulions. Nous sommes encerclés ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:195
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:205
msgid "If you'll permit me to say so, sir, you're wrong. We could - "
msgstr ""
"Si vous me le permettez, Monsieur, vous vous trompez. Nous pourrions - "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:199
msgid ""
"Shut up, Baglur! You don't know what you're talking about. I've analyzed the "
"situation, and we're doomed. Our best hope is to surrender. Perhaps if we "
"give the elves the plans for the sceptre they will let us survive."
msgstr ""
"Tais-toi, Baglur ! Tu ne sais pas de quoi tu parles. J'ai analysé la "
"situation, et nous sommes condamnés. Notre meilleur espoir est de nous "
"rendre. Peut-être que si nous donnons les plans du sceptre aux elfes, ils "
"nous laisseront vivre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Shut up, Rugnur! You don't know what you're talking about. I've analyzed the "
"situation, and we're doomed. Our best hope is to surrender. Perhaps if we "
"give the elves the plans for the sceptre they will let us survive."
msgstr ""
"Tais-toi, Rugnur! Tu ne sais pas de quoi tu parles. J'ai analysé la "
"situation, et nous sommes condamnés. Notre meilleur espoir est de nous "
"rendre. Peut-être que si nous donnons les plans du sceptre aux elfes, ils "
"nous laisserons vivre."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:215
msgid ""
"Yes, of course, let's just all be cowards! What happened to your honor, "
"Durstorn?!"
msgstr ""
"Oui, bien sûr, devenons tous des lâches ! Qu'en est-il de ton honneur, "
"Durstorn ?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:219
msgid ""
"You little fool, honor is less important than life! So, I'm ordering "
"Thursagan to give the plans and the ruby to the elves, as a peace offering. "
"Then maybe we'll walk out of here alive."
msgstr ""
"Imbécile ! L'honneur est moins important que la vie ! Donc je donne l'ordre "
"à Thursagan de donner les plans et le rubis aux elfes, comme gage de paix. "
"Ensuite nous pourrons peut-être partir vivants. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:223
msgid ""
"You don't have authority over me, Durstorn. And I wouldn't give the sceptre "
"to them even if you did. It's not yours to give, its mine, and Rugnur's, and "
"Baglur's. Krawg's done more for its existence than you have! And yet, you "
"still get the profits from selling it to Haldric."
msgstr ""
"Tu n'as pas autorité sur moi, Durstorn. Je ne leur donnerais pas le sceptre, "
"même si tu le ferais. Il n'est pas à toi, il est à moi, et à Rugnur, et à "
"Baglur. Krawg a fait plus pour son existence que toi ! Et pourtant, c'est "
"encore toi qui reçois les bénéfices de la vente à Haldric. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:227
msgid ""
"So what, all of you want to die? Fine by me, but I won't die with you! And "
"if you won't give the sceptre to the elves, I'll take it from you!"
msgstr ""
"Et alors, vous voulez tous mourir ? Faites comme vous voulez, mais je ne "
"mourrai pas avec vous ! Et si vous ne donnez pas le sceptre aux elfes, je "
"vous le prendrai !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:232
msgid " *swoosh*"
msgstr " *swoosh*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:236
msgid ""
"Nice try, Durstorn, but you missed. Now, I'd say that attacking an ally "
"constitutes treason, wouldn't you?"
msgstr ""
"Bien essayé, Durstorn, mais tu as raté. Maintenant, je dirais qu'attaquer un "
"allié constitue une trahison, pas toi ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:240
msgid ""
"You're not my ally. You're more against me than the elves are; all they want "
"is the ruby, but you want us dead!"
msgstr ""
"Tu n'es pas mon allié. Tu es pour moi un plus grand ennemi que les elfes ; "
"tout ce qu'ils veulent, c'est le rubis, mais toi, tu veux notre mort ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:244
msgid ""
"If that's what you're thinking, you're not fit to be ruler over us! So step "
"down, or we'll force you."
msgstr ""
"Si c'est ce que tu penses, tu ne peux plus nous diriger ! Abdique, ou nous "
"t'y forcerons."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:248
msgid "Never!"
msgstr "Jamais !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:253
msgid " *thud*"
msgstr " *thud*"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:262
msgid ""
"Well, I suppose we were right to silence him, but I don't like this. In any "
"case, now we should try to get out of here."
msgstr ""
"Bon, je suppose que nous avons eu raison de le réduire au silence, mais je "
"n'aime pas ça. En tout cas, nous devrions essayer de sortir d'ici."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:266
msgid "Yes. So, see the area to the northeast of us?"
msgstr "Oui. Bon, tu vois la zone au nord-est ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:276
msgid ""
"That's where there are the least elvish guards, so we have the greatest "
"chance of success there. I think we should try to get to it."
msgstr ""
"C'est là qu'il y a le moins de gardes elfes, c'est donc là que nous avons la "
"plus grande chance de succès. Je pense que nous devrions essayer d'aller par "
"là."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:280
msgid ""
"This plan, it isn't worse than staying here to be killed, but it isn't "
"likely to succeed either. Even if it does, what will it accomplish? We will "
"be cornered there."
msgstr ""
"Même si ce plan n'est pas pire que de se faire tuer ici, ce n'est pas pour "
"ça qu'il a beaucoup de chances de réussir. Et même s'il réussit, où en "
"serons-nous ? On sera coincé dans un coin."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:284
msgid ""
"I don't know if we will be cornered. That cave looks like it goes deep, and "
"we can lose the elves in the caves, they move so slow there."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais pas si nous serons coincés. Cette caverne me semble descendre "
"bien profondément, et nous pouvons semer les elfes dans les cavernes. Ils "
"s'y déplacent si lentement."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:288
msgid ""
"That's fine for you, you can run fast in caves, but I can't! What am I "
"supposed to do?"
msgstr ""
"Oui, ça va pour toi qui peux courir vite dans les cavernes, mais moi, je ne "
"peux pas ! Qu'est-ce que je suis censé faire ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:292
msgid ""
"Well, you are a member of the Wesnothian army. Why don't you rejoin it? See "
"if you can run past those elves to our southeast,"
msgstr ""
"Eh bien... Tu es un membre de l'armée de Wesnoth. Pourquoi ne la rejoins-tu "
"pas ? Vois si tu peux passer au travers des elfes au sud-est."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:302
msgid "And then ride south until you reach one of your outposts."
msgstr ""
"Et ensuite file vers le sud jusqu'à ce que tu trouves un de tes avant-postes."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:306
msgid ""
"I'm not going to do that, its suicide! And in any case, I've been with you "
"for 10 years, almost as long as I was in the Wesnothian army; I'd prefer to "
"fight with you."
msgstr ""
"Je ne vais pas faire ça, c'est du suicide ! Et dans tous les cas, je suis "
"resté avec toi depuis 10 ans, presque aussi longtemps que je n'ai été dans "
"l'armée de Wesnoth ; je préférerais me battre avec toi. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:310
msgid ""
"You going south has more of a chance of success for you than staying here or "
"going to the caves! And getting news to Haldric of what has happened is also "
"the best way to get help to us."
msgstr ""
"Que tu ailles au sud a plus de chance de succès pour toi que de rester ici "
"ou de venir dans les souterrains ! Et donner des nouvelles à Haldric sur ce "
"qui c'est passé ici est aussi la meilleure façon de nous aider."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:314
msgid "I suppose..."
msgstr "Je suppose..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:318
msgid "Come out, dwarves, and surrender! Or die in that cave, your choice."
msgstr ""
"Sortez, nains, et rendez-vous ! Ou bien mourrez dans ces cavernes, comme "
"vous voulez."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:352
msgid ""
"Alanin, ride as fast as you can south. Tell Haldric we are going into a "
"cave, and to send forces to help us as soon as he can!"
msgstr ""
"Alanin, fonce au sud le plus vite que tu peux. Dis à Haldric que nous allons "
"dans ces cavernes et envoie des forces pour nous aider, le plus tôt, le "
"mieux."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:392
msgid ""
"I have made it past those elves, but they will chase me, and elvish horses "
"are faster than mine."
msgstr ""
"J'ai pu passer au travers des elfes, mais ils vont me prendre en chasse, et "
"les chevaux elfes sont plus rapides que le mien. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:422
msgid "Rugnur, I am going south. What should I tell Haldric?"
msgstr "Rugnur, je vais au sud. Que dois-je dire à Haldric ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:426
msgid ""
"Tell him to send forces north to aid us and fight the elves, but that we are "
"probably going to die. We are going into the caves."
msgstr ""
"Dis-lui d'envoyer des forces au nord pour nous aider à combattre les elfes, "
"mais que nous allons probablement mourir. Nous allons dans ces cavernes. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/6_Towards_the_Caves.cfg:473
msgid ""
"I don't know what is in these caves, but whatever it is can't be worse than "
"staying here to die."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais pas ce qu'il y a dans ces cavernes, mais ça ne peut pas être pire "
"que de rester ici et d'y mourir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:3
msgid "Outriding the Outriders"
msgstr "Semer les poursuivants"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:57
msgid ""
"Rugnur had fled to the caves, but Alanin could not do that. He went south - "
"back to the Wesnoth border."
msgstr ""
"Rugnur avait fui vers les cavernes, mais Alanin ne pouvait pas faire ça. Il "
"partit au sud, en direction de la frontière de Wesnoth."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:60
msgid ""
"The elves followed both of them. First I will tell of their persuit of "
"Alanin, before we descent into the caves to learn Rugnur's fate."
msgstr ""
"Les elfes les suivirent tous les deux. D'abord je raconterai la poursuite "
"d'Alanin, ensuite nous redescendrons dans les sous-sols pour connaitre le "
"destin de Rugnur."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:77
msgid "Reach the Wesnothian outpost in the south"
msgstr "Rejoindre l'avant-poste wesnothien au sud"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:104
msgid ""
"Well, the elves are behind me for now, but they will send riders to catch "
"me, and elvish riders are faster than me."
msgstr ""
"Bon, les elfes sont derrière moi, maintenant, mais ils vont envoyer des "
"cavaliers pour m'attraper, et les cavaliers elfes sont plus rapides que moi."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:108
msgid ""
"My only hope is to convince the peasants to stop the elves from passing "
"through their land, so I can get ahead of them."
msgstr ""
"Mon seul espoir est de convaincre les paysans d'empêcher les elfes de passer "
"par leurs champs, pour que je puisse conserver mon avance. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:117
msgid "Lord Asaeri"
msgstr "Lord Asaeri"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:128
msgid "Gaelir"
msgstr "Gaelir"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:139
msgid "Salira"
msgstr "Salira"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:150
msgid "Losnin"
msgstr "Losnin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:161
msgid "Ealin"
msgstr "Ealin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:177
msgid ""
"You cannot outride us, horseman of Wesnoth! Whatever message you are "
"carrying, it will not be delivered!"
msgstr ""
"Tu ne pourras pas nous échapper, cavalier de Wesnoth ! Quelque soir le "
"message que tu portes, il ne sera pas délivré ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:181
msgid "We shall see about that!"
msgstr "Nous allons voir ça !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:190
msgid "Raesil"
msgstr "Raesil"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:207
msgid ""
"The villagers here are loyal to Wesnoth. They should be willing to help me "
"escape these elves!"
msgstr ""
"Les villageois de cette région sont fidèles à Wesnoth. Ils devraient "
"accepter de m'aider à échapper à ces elfes ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:212
msgid "Rolin"
msgstr "Rolin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:217
msgid "We will certainly help any warrior of Wesnoth who needs our help!"
msgstr "Nous aiderons volontiers tout homme de Wesnoth qui en a besoin !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:244
msgid "Hadlin"
msgstr "Hadlin"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:249
msgid "Who goes there?"
msgstr "Qui va là ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:253
msgid ""
"I'm a dragoon, with Haldric II's personal bodyguard. I was sent on a mission "
"in the northlands, and now elvish horsemen are chasing me. I barely evaded "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Je suis un dragon, de la garde personnelle d'Haldric II. J'étais en mission "
"dans le nord, et maintenant, les cavaliers elfes sont à ma poursuite. Je "
"leur ai presque échappé."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/7_Outriding_of_Outriders.cfg:257
msgid ""
"I see. Well, come on in. I doubt they would be able to capture this fort, "
"even if they did want to start a war, which I doubt."
msgstr ""
"Je vois. Bon, venez par ici. Je doute qu'ils soient capables de prendre ce "
"fort, même s'ils voulaient commencer une guerre, ce dont je doute."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:3
msgid "The Dragon"
msgstr "Le Dragon"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:32
msgid "Landar"
msgstr "Landar"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:51
msgid "Khrakrahs"
msgstr "Khrakrahs"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:68
msgid ""
"Thus Alanin escaped from his Elvish pursuers. But the dwarves were not so "
"lucky. I would say that, perhaps, their betrayal of Durstorn was coming back "
"to haunt them. For unknown to them, they had entered the caves of "
"Khrakhrahs... the dragon."
msgstr ""
"Donc Alanin échappa à ses poursuivants elfes. Mais les nains n'eurent pas "
"cette chance. Je dirais que, peut-être, leur trahison de Durstorn revint les "
"hanter. Car, à leur insu, ils étaient entrés dans la caverne de "
"Khrakhrahs... le dragon."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:85
msgid "Get all heroes to the end of the tunnel"
msgstr "Amener tous les héros à la fin du tunnel. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:184
msgid ""
"Well, Thursagan, we've reached the caves, but the elves are hot on our "
"trail. What do we do now?"
msgstr ""
"Voila, Thursagan, nous avons atteint les cavernes, mais les elfes sont sur "
"nos talons. Que devons-nous faire, maintenant ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:188
msgid ""
"Well, we have two choices. We may either stand and fight, and assuredly die, "
"or run as quickly as possible down this path into the depths of the cave, "
"where we may find something that will help us. Also, remember, the elves "
"can't run as fast in caves as we can, so we may be able to get ahead of them "
"and perhaps lay a trap."
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, nous avons deux possibilités. Nous pouvons rester ici et nous "
"défendre, et sûrement mourir, ou courir le plus vite possible vers le fond "
"de cette caverne, où nous pourrons peut-être trouver quelque chose qui nous "
"aidera. Souvenez-vous aussi que les elfes ne peuvent pas courir aussi vite "
"que nous dans les cavernes, donc nous pouvons partir en avance sur eux, et "
"peut-être leur préparer un piège. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:192
msgid "Why don't we just surrender? All they want is that magic stone!"
msgstr ""
"Pourquoi est-ce qu'on ne peut pas simplement se rendre ? Tout ce qu'ils "
"veulent, c'est cette pierre magique ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:196
msgid ""
"If we give them the ruby, then what? They'll probably kill us anyway. And, "
"that ruby has the power to do great things, evil things. We can't let it "
"fall into the wrong hands."
msgstr ""
"Si nous lui donnons le rubis, que se passera-t-il ? Ils nous tueront de "
"toute façon. Et ce rubis a le pouvoir de faire de grandes choses, des choses "
"terribles. Nous ne pouvons pas le laisser tomber entre de mauvaises mains."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:205
msgid ""
"So we're running away, eh? I don't like that, but it seems it's our only "
"option."
msgstr ""
"Donc, nous allons courir, hein ? Je n'aime pas ça, mais on dirait que c'est "
"notre seule option. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:209
msgid "If it makes you feel any better, we'll probably die this way, too."
msgstr ""
"Si ça peut te rassurer, nous allons probablement mourir comme ça aussi."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:222
msgid "Look, there's a dragon in these caves!"
msgstr "Regardez, il y a un dragon dans cette caverne !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:226
msgid "Ah, fresh meat!"
msgstr "Ah, de la viande fraîche ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:230
msgid "And which of the great dragons are you?"
msgstr "Et lequel des grands dragons êtes-vous ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:234
msgid ""
"I am Khrakrahs, greatest dragon of all time! Haldric killed Shek'kahan my "
"brother, but he was weaker than me, and you will not find me so easy to "
"defeat. Now get out of my volcano!"
msgstr ""
"Je suis Khrakrahs, le plus grand des dragons de tous les temps ! Haldric a "
"tué Shek'kahan, mon frère, mais il était plus faible que moi, et vous ne me "
"trouverez pas si facile à tuer. Maintenant, sortez de mon volcan !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:238
msgid ""
"I'd rather face one powerful dragon than hundreds of mighty elves. Continue!"
msgstr ""
"Je préfère encore combattre un puissant dragon que des centaines d'elfes. On "
"continue !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:250
msgid "What's this? A dwarf fighting against us with the elves?!"
msgstr "Qu'est-ce que c'est que ça ? Un nain qui nous combat avec les elfes ?!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:254
msgid ""
"It must be one of those Surghan mercenaries. I'll bet those elves have hired "
"more of them. That's bad news for us, for they'll go as fast in caves as we "
"do."
msgstr ""
"Il doit être l'un de ces mercenaires de Surghan. Je parierais que ces elfes "
"en ont enrôlés plusieurs. C'est une mauvaise nouvelle pour nous, parce "
"qu'ils vont courir aussi vite que nous dans ces cavernes. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:271
msgid ""
"Look, I've found something here. It looks like a forge, heated by the lava. "
"It looks magic, and it looks hot enough to make the Sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Regardez, j'ai trouvé quelque chose ici. On dirait une forge, chauffée par "
"la lave. Elle a l'air magique, et je pense qu'elle est assez chaude pour "
"faire le sceptre. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:275
msgid "That pretty metal rock is mine! Get away from it!"
msgstr "Cette jolie pierre en métal est à moi. Éloignez-vous d'elle ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:280
msgid "Move Thursagan to the forge"
msgstr "Déplacer Thursagan vers la forge."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:284
msgid "Defend Thursagan until the sceptre is complete"
msgstr "Défendre Thursagan jusqu'à ce que le sceptre soit fini."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:314
msgid ""
"This forge will work perfectly. Give me a few days here, and I can reforge "
"the sceptre to fulfil its purpose."
msgstr ""
"Cette forge conviendra parfaitement. Donnez-moi quelques jours, et je "
"pourrai reforger le sceptre pour qu'il remplissent son rôle."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:323
msgid "Survive for 9 turns"
msgstr "Survivre 9 tours"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:335
msgid "An enemy moves onto the forge"
msgstr "Un ennemi entre dans la forge "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:360
msgid "You fool, you let the enemy get at me as I was unarmed!"
msgstr ""
"Imbécile, vous avez laissé un ennemi arriver jusqu'à moi, alors que j'étais "
"désarmé ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:115
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:366
msgid "Ayahahh..."
msgstr "Ayahahh..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:390
msgid ""
"I have completed my work. Now it is truly the Sceptre of Fire, a powerful "
"magical artifact."
msgstr ""
"Voila, mon travail est fini. Maintenant, c'est vraiment le Sceptre de Feu, "
"un puissant objet magique. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:394
msgid ""
"Good. Now, let's get out of this cave, before the elves, dwarves or bats "
"kill us!"
msgstr ""
"Bien. Maintenant, sortons de ces caves, avant que les elfes, les nains ou "
"les chauves-souris ne nous tuent !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/8_The_Dragon.cfg:409
msgid "In $turnsleft more turns I will have completed the sceptre."
msgstr "Dans $turnsleft tours de plus, j'aurai fini le sceptre. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:3
msgid "Caverns of Flame"
msgstr "Les Cavernes enflammées"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:131
msgid ""
"There was no exit from the caverns of Knalga. They had reached the realms of "
"the orcs, with the elves hot on their trail. And there was no exit from "
"those caves."
msgstr ""
"Il n'y avait pas de sortie aux cavernes de Knalga. Ils avaient atteint le "
"domaine des orcs, avec les elfes sur leurs talons. Et il n'y avait pas de "
"sortie à ces souterrains."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:134
msgid ""
"So the dwarves had no way out. They could not leave the caverns that they "
"had entered."
msgstr ""
"Les nains n'avaient donc pas d'issue. Ils ne pouvaient pas quitter les "
"cavernes dans lesquelles ils étaient entrés."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:153
msgid "Explore as much of the cave as possible"
msgstr "Explorer le plus de cavernes possible"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:225
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:233
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:241
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:249
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:257
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:265
msgid "Guardian"
msgstr "Garde "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:270
msgid ""
"Well, I think we've gotten a good distance ahead of the elves. What do we do "
"now?"
msgstr ""
"Bien, je pense que nous avons pris une bonne avance sur les elfes. Que "
"faisons-nous, maintenant ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:274
msgid ""
"We should keep going. Remember what Khrakrahs said, about this being a "
"volcano? I think we should try to cause it to erupt. It will kill all the "
"elves, and we might be able to find a safe place so the lava doesn't kill us."
msgstr ""
"Nous devrions continuer. Vous rappelez-vous ce que Khrakrahs a dit, que ceci "
"est un volcan ? Je pense que nous devrions essayer de le faire entrer en "
"éruption. Cela tuera les elfes et nous pourrions trouver un endroit sûr où "
"la lave ne nous tuera pas. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:278
msgid "This sounds... attemptable."
msgstr "Ça à l'air ... possible. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:282
msgid "Yes, an interesting plan. How do you propose we do this?"
msgstr ""
"Oui, c'est un plan intéressant. Comment comptes-tu que nous fassions cela ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:286
msgid ""
"I have a suspicion that there is an opening somewhere near here than leads "
"to the surface. Somewhere near there, there is probably a magic object of "
"some kind that will cause the lava to flow."
msgstr ""
"Je soupçonne qu'il y ait une ouverture du côté de celle qui mène à la "
"surface. Pas loin d'ici, il doit probablement y avoir un objet magique "
"quelconque qui permettra à la lave de couler. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:290
msgid "Very well. We will continue to explore until we find it."
msgstr ""
"Très bien. Nous allons continuer à explorer jusqu'à ce que nous le trouvions."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:295
msgid "Krawg sme' o'cz in iz 'ave!"
msgstr "Krawg dez o'cz ans c't 'ave ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:299
msgid "Indeed, there may be orcs lurking here. We should beware of them."
msgstr ""
"En effet, il peut y avoir des orcs dans le coin. Nous devons faire attention "
"à eux."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:327
msgid "Aendan"
msgstr "Aendan"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:333
msgid "We have caught up to the dwarves. Now, prepare to destroy them!"
msgstr ""
"Nous avons attrapé les nains. Maintenant, préparez-vous à les éliminer !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:372
msgid "Thursagan! The elves are right on our tail; what should we do?"
msgstr "Thursagan ! Les elfes sont sur nos talons ; que devons-nous faire ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:376
msgid ""
"We could try to set off the volcano as soon as possible. Meanwhile, we "
"should draw the elves further into the caves, so they can't escape when it "
"does erupt."
msgstr ""
"Nous pourrions essayer de lancer l'éruption du volcan le plus vite possible. "
"Entre-temps, nous devrions conduire les elfes plus loin dans les cavernes, "
"pour qu'ils ne puissent pas échapper à l'éruption."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:436
msgid "These orcs appear to be guarding something."
msgstr "Il semblerait que ces orcs gardent quelque chose."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:440
msgid "It is probably the magical object. Attack them!"
msgstr "C'est sûrement l'objet magique. Attaquez-les !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:445
msgid "Move onto the glyph in the center of the volcano"
msgstr "Déplacez-vous jusqu'au glyphe au centre du volcan."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:508
msgid "That's it! The volcano will erupt soon now that you've triggered it."
msgstr ""
"Ça y est ! Le volcan entrera en éruption dès que nous l'aurons allumé. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:519
msgid ""
"Look, it has knocked down some of the walls! Those orcs have a way out now!"
msgstr ""
"Regardez, il a abattu un des murs ! Ces orcs peuvent sortir, maintenant !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:528
msgid ""
"Well, we've succeeded in stopping the elves from getting the sceptre, I "
"would say. But what do we do now?!"
msgstr ""
"Bien, je dirais que nous avons réussi à empêcher les elfes de prendre le "
"sceptre. Mais que devons nous faire, maintenant ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:534
msgid "Now, we must fight the orcs until we die, it's our only option."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, nous devons combattre ces orcs jusqu'à la mort, c'est notre "
"seule option."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:540
msgid ""
"We cannot let any of the elves or their mercenaries escape; they would tell "
"where the sceptre is. Make sure they all die!"
msgstr ""
"Nous ne pouvons laisser aucun des elfes ou de leur mercenaire s'échapper; "
"ils diraient où est le sceptre. Assurez-vous qu'ils meurent tous !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:546
msgid ""
"We have to kill them quickly, before they realize what is happening. And "
"remember, the lava spreads quickly, suddenly, and dangerously. The only "
"place safe from it is the area near the glyph."
msgstr ""
"Nous devons les tuer rapidement, avant qu'ils ne réalisent ce qui leur "
"arrive. Et souvenez-vous que la lave se répand rapidement, soudainement, et "
"dangereusement. Le seul endroit sûr est la zone près du glyphe."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:578
msgid ""
"Wait, what's going on? The volcano is going to erupt! Everyone, try to get "
"out of these caves!"
msgstr ""
"Attendez, que ce passe-t-il ? Le volcan est en train d'entrer en éruption ! "
"Que tout le monde essaye de sortir ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:596
msgid "I must go report to my superiors!"
msgstr "Je dois aller prévenir mes supérieurs ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:601
msgid "We have allowed an enemy to escape; we have failed."
msgstr "Nous avons laisser un ennemi s'échapper ; nous avons échoué. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:658
msgid ""
"Aghh!!! The volcano is erupting, and now our exit has been blocked off!!!"
msgstr ""
"Arghh!!! Le volcan est en éruption et maintenant notre sortie a été "
"bloquée !!!  "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:683
msgid ""
"We have hidden the sceptre well, but now the volcano is going to erupt and "
"kill us all."
msgstr ""
"Nous avons bien caché le sceptre, mais maintenant, le volcan va entrer en "
"éruption et il nous tuera tous."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:818
msgid "Kill all of the elves before one of them escapes from the caves"
msgstr "Tuer tous les elfes avant que l'un d'eux ne s'échappe de la caverne"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/9_Caverns_of_Flame.cfg:925
msgid "Hm... Me le' no'w!"
msgstr "Hm... Me le' no'w!"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:3
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Épilogue "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:39
msgid ""
"And thus Rugnur died, a glorious death, in the eyes of the dwarven sages. "
"But our tale is not yet complete. For Alanin lived still, as did Krawg the "
"Gryphon."
msgstr ""
"Et c'est ainsi que Rugnur mourut d'une mort glorieuse aux yeux des sages "
"nains. Mais notre légende n'est pas encore finie. Car Alanin avait survécu, "
"ainsi que Krawg le griffon."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:42
msgid ""
"Alanin traveled south, to Wesnoth, to Haldric II. To report the events of "
"the past fifteen years."
msgstr ""
"Alanin voyagea en direction du sud, vers Wesnoth, vers Haldric II. Pour "
"rapporter les évènements des quinze dernières années."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:45
msgid ""
"And Krawg - well, Krawg followed him. I know not how. But Krawg made his way "
"south, to Weldyn, and reached it about the time that Alanin did."
msgstr ""
"Et Krawg. Eh bien, Krawg le suivit. Je ne sais pas comment, mais Krawg fila "
"au sud jusque Weldyn et l'atteignit presque en même temps qu'Alanin."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:84
msgid "Guard Captain"
msgstr "Capitaine de la garde "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:101
msgid "Gatekeeper"
msgstr "Gardien de la porte"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:117
msgid "Halt! What is your business in Weldyn, capital of Wesnoth?"
msgstr "Halte ! Que venez-vous faire à Weldyn, capitale de Wesnoth ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:121
msgid ""
"Stand aside. I am Alanin, of Haldric's royal guard, and I bring news from "
"the northlands."
msgstr ""
"Écarte-toi. Je suis Alanin, de la Garde Royale d'Haldric, et j'apporte des "
"nouvelles des contrées du nord. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:125
msgid "Very well. You may pass."
msgstr "Très bien. Vous pouvez passer."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:130
msgid ""
"I hear you desire to speak to the king, Alanin. What do you have to tell him?"
msgstr ""
"J'ai entendu ton désir de parler au roi, Alanin. Que veux-tu lui dire ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:134
msgid ""
"I bring tidings of the Sceptre of Fire, commissioned fifteen years ago by "
"our king. I have been away for a long time, do not delay me even more."
msgstr ""
"J'apporte des nouvelles à propos du Sceptre de Feu, commandé il y a quinze "
"ans par notre roi. Je suis resté loin pendant longtemps, ne me retarde pas "
"encore plus."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:138
msgid "Enter, Alanin, and give the king your message."
msgstr "Entre, Alanin, et délivre ton message au roi. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:164
msgid ""
"My King, fifteen years ago you sent me on a mission into the northlands. I "
"have returned. What do you wish to know of my mission?"
msgstr ""
"Mon Roi, il y a quinze ans, vous m'avez envoyé en mission dans les contrées "
"du nord. Je suis revenu. Que désirez-vous savoir sur ma mission ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:168
msgid "Well, was the Sceptre completed? Do you have it? Give it to me!"
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, est-ce que le Sceptre a été fabriqué ? L'as-tu ? Donne-le moi !"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:172
msgid ""
"I believe it was completed, but, I do not have it. It is buried deep in the "
"mountains of the Northlands."
msgstr ""
"Je pense qu'il était fini, mais je ne l'ai pas. Il est enterré profondément "
"dans les montagnes des contrées du nord. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Why? Why was it not returned to me? Have the dwarves reneged on their "
"promise, and kept it?"
msgstr ""
"Pourquoi ? Pourquoi ne me l'a-t-on pas rendu ? Est-ce que les nains ont "
"renié leur promesse et l'ont gardé ? "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:180
msgid ""
"My Lord, the dwarves are dead, slain by fire and smoke as lava poured out of "
"one of the mountains. I saw the eruption from afar as I was returning to you."
msgstr ""
"Monseigneur, les nains sont morts, abattus par le feu et la fumée quand la "
"lave est sortie d'une des montagnes. J'ai vu l'éruption de loin, alors que "
"je revenais vers vous."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:184
msgid "Why were you returning without the sceptre, then?"
msgstr "Pourquoi es-tu revenu sans le Sceptre, alors ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:188
msgid ""
"We had been besieged by elves, in a dwarvish castle that was not Rugnur's. "
"The sceptre could not be completed there, but it could in a cave that lay to "
"the northeast of it. Rugnur sent me back, with the message that it had been "
"completed, but he and all the rest of the dwarves went into the caves, and "
"were immediately followed by hundreds of elves."
msgstr ""
"Nous étions assiégés par les elfes, dans un château nain qui n'appartenait "
"pas à Rugnur. Le Sceptre n'a pas pu être fini à cet endroit, mais il pouvait "
"l'être dans une caverne un peu plus au nord-est. Rugnur m'a renvoyé, avec le "
"message qu'il avait fini le travail, mais que lui et le reste des nains "
"partaient par les cavernes, et qu'ils étaient poursuivis par des centaines "
"d'elfes. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:192
msgid ""
"If the sceptre was not completed in your sight, what makes you so sure it "
"exists?"
msgstr "Si tu n'as pas vu le Sceptre prêt, comment es-tu sûr qu'il existe ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:196
msgid "I will let Krawg explain that."
msgstr "Je laisserais Krawg expliquer ça."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:200
msgid "Who?"
msgstr "Qui ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:222
msgid ""
"My lord, a gryphon has just flown over our walls! It may be a sign of an "
"attack!"
msgstr ""
"Monseigneur, un griffon vient juste de passer au-dessus de nos murs ! Cela "
"pourrait être le signe d'une attaque ! "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:226
msgid ""
"No, that is my... friend Krawg. He went with Rugnur into the caves, but "
"escaped through a hole in the roof right before the lava filled the cave."
msgstr ""
"Non, c'est mon ... ami Krawg. Il était avec Rugnur dans les cavernes, mais "
"il s'est échappé par une ouverture dans le plafond juste avant que la lave "
"remplisse la caverne."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:231
msgid "Ya, ya! Meh seah za zeptahur. Hrugnaar ha ee. Lozeet enda caav."
msgstr "Koui, koui ! Ja vour 'e zeptahur. Kouoi ha uu. E'hu enda caav."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:235
msgid "What the devil is he saying?"
msgstr "Que diable dit-il ?"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:239
msgid ""
"He says that he has seen the Sceptre. Rugnur had it, but he lost it in the "
"caves. He came to tell you, so that you would know that the dwarves did "
"fulfil their promise."
msgstr ""
"Il a dit qu'il a vu le Sceptre. Rugnur l'avait, mais il l'a perdu dans la "
"caverne. Il est venu vous le dire, pour que vous sachiez que les nains ont "
"tenu leur promesse. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:244
msgid "Kreeeeya! Darat! Nomiduun. Bah."
msgstr "Kreeeeya! Darat! Nomiduun. Bah."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:248
msgid ""
"I see. Well... what do you want me to do now? The sceptre is made, yes, but "
"I don't know where it is, the makers are dead, and orcs have probably "
"already found it and hid it somewhere else."
msgstr ""
"Je vois. Bon... Que veux-tu que je fasse, maintenant ? Le Sceptre est fait, "
"oui, mais je ne sais pas où il est, ses artisans sont morts, et les orcs "
"l'ont probablement déjà trouvé et caché quelque part ailleurs. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:252
msgid ""
"I do not know. I only bring the news, I did not cause it, nor do I fully "
"understand its implications. But, my advice would be to do nothing. I "
"believe you will not find it, though you send a hundred armies to look for "
"it. But record in the history books that the sceptre does exist."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais pas. Je ne fais qu'apporter les nouvelles, je ne les ai pas "
"causées, et je ne comprends pas non plus leurs implications. Mais mon "
"conseil serait de ne rien faire. Je pense que vous ne le retrouverez pas, "
"même en envoyant une centaine d'armées pour le chercher. Mais écrivez dans "
"les livres d'histoire que le Sceptre existe bien. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:256
msgid ""
"Your advice seems good to me. I will take it. As for you, and the gryphon, "
"you are free to go. Alanin, you've served in the army long enough to retire, "
"and even if you hadn't, you've seen enough combat. So, go. Back to your "
"village. You deserve a rest."
msgstr ""
"Tes conseils me plaisent. Je vais les appliquer. Quant à toi, et le griffon, "
"vous êtes libre de partir. Alanin, tu as servi l'armée suffisamment "
"longtemps pour prendre ta retraite. Même si tu n'y as pas participé, tu as "
"vu suffisamment de combats. Retourne dans ton village. Tu mérites le repos. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:260
msgid "Very well, my lord."
msgstr "Très bien, Monseigneur."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:264
msgid ""
"The sceptre would not be found until many generations after Haldric II, in "
"the time of Asheviere the Dark Queen. During that time, it sat in the caves "
"of the Northlands, unfound but undestroyed, moved around by Orcs who never "
"understood its true power."
msgstr ""
"Le Sceptre ne sera pas retrouvé avant de nombreuses générations après "
"Haldric II, au temps d'Ashevière, la reine sombre. Pendant tout ce temps, il "
"resta dans les cavernes des contrées du nord, jamais découvert, mais jamais "
"détruit, déplacé au gré des orcs qui n'ont jamais compris son pouvoir."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/Epilogue.cfg:268
msgid ""
"But before it was found, legends grew up around it, and around its makers - "
"Thursagan, most brilliant of the Dwarven Sages, and Rugnur, the greatest of "
"the Dwarven Heroes of old."
msgstr ""
"Mais avant qu'il ne soit retrouvé, des légendes ont fleuri à son propos et à "
"propos de ses artisans - Thursagan, le plus brillant des sages nains, et "
"Rugnur, le plus grand des héros nains de tous les temps. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:53
msgid "Gahahh..."
msgstr "Gahahh..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:66
msgid "Maghah..."
msgstr "Maghah..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:79
msgid "Ahhgg..."
msgstr "Ahhgg..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/scenarios/utils/utils.cfg:102
msgid "Kraa..."
msgstr "Kraa..."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Caravan.cfg:4
msgid "Caravan"
msgstr "Caravane"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Caravan.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Caravans are used to carry gold or supplies long distances. Because of the "
"immense weight of the cargo this caravan carries, it moves very slowly."
msgstr ""
"Les caravanes sont utilisées pour transporter l'or et les marchandises sur "
"de longues distances. Elle se déplace très lentement à cause de son grand "
"poids. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Arcanister.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Arcanister"
msgstr "Faiseur d'arcanes nain "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Arcanister.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The most powerful of all the runecrafters, the Dwarvish Arcanister destroys "
"wounded enemies almost instantly, and rarely fails to cause a wound when "
"that is his intent. His skill in runecrafting is unrivaled, and the glyphs "
"he carves into his weapons and armor deflect the blows of his enemies."
msgstr ""
"Le plus puissant de tous les tailleurs de runes, le faiseur d'arcanes nain "
"détruit les ennemis blessés presque instantanément, et parvient souvent à "
"infliger une blessure quand il le veut. Sa capacité à tailler les runes est "
"inégalée et les glyphes gravés sur ses armes et son armure détournent les "
"coups de ses ennemis. "

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:25
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:26
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Arcanister.cfg:26
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Arcanister.cfg:27
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runesmith.cfg:28
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runesmith.cfg:29
msgid "hammer"
msgstr "marteau"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:27
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Arcanister.cfg:28
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runesmith.cfg:30
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Haldric_II.cfg:22
msgid "impact"
msgstr "impact"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Miner.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Miner"
msgstr "Mineur nain."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Miner.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Dwarvish miners are the grunt workers of Dwarvish society. They take the "
"precious ores out of the ground, but do not ever take part in the crafting "
"of weapons or artifacts."
msgstr ""
"Les mineurs nains sont les petites mains de la société naine. Ils arrachent "
"les matières précieuses de la terre sans jamais prendre part à la "
"fabrication des armes et des artéfacts."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Miner.cfg:18
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Miner.cfg:19
msgid "pick"
msgstr "pique"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Wolf.cfg:29
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Miner.cfg:20
msgid "pierce"
msgstr "perce"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Runemaster"
msgstr "Maître des runes nain"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runemaster.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Except for those with almost supernatural skill, the highest rank a "
"runecrafter can rise to is that of the Dwarvish Runemaster. Striking blows "
"nearly as powerful as those of the best warriors, they would be fearsome "
"without their craft, but with it they are also nigh on invincible, since "
"their runes cause the physical blows of their enemies to deal less damage "
"than would be expected."
msgstr ""
"Mis à part avec des capacités surnaturelles, le plus haut rang qu'un graveur "
"de runes peut atteindre est maître des runes nain. Frappant presque aussi "
"puissamment que les meilleurs guerriers, ils n'ont déjà peur de rien sans "
"leur arme, mais quand ils l'ont, ils sont presque invincibles car leurs "
"runes diminue les dégâts causés par les coups de leurs ennemis."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runesmith.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Runesmith"
msgstr "Forgeron des runes nain"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Dwarvish_Runesmith.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Dwarvish runesmiths, now practiced at their craft, carve arcane runes into "
"their weapons and armor. These runes infuse the runesmith's blows with power "
"and accuracy, and disrupt the blows of their enemies, causing them to strike "
"softly, weakly and on the armor of the defender."
msgstr ""
"Les forgerons des runes nains, maintenant habitués à leur art, gravent des "
"runes sur leurs armes et armures. Ces runes imprègnent les coups du forgeron "
"de puissance et de précision et détournent les coups des ennemis, adoucis et "
"faibles quand ils frappent sur l'armure."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Haldric_II.cfg:4
msgid "King"
msgstr "Roi"

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Haldric_II.cfg:17
msgid "King of Wesnoth."
msgstr "Le roi de Wesnoth."

#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Haldric_II.cfg:20
#: data/campaigns/Sceptre_of_Fire/units/Haldric_II.cfg:21
msgid "punch"
msgstr "coup de poing"

